channel.title: [PI] What is wrong with this command?
channel.description:
[code]src\server\model\players\packets\Commands.java:347: cannot find symbol symbol : variable voteDelay location: class server.model.players.Client if((Long.parseLong(c.voteDelay) - System.currentTimeMillis()) > 0) { ^ src\server\model\players\packets\Commands.java:350: cannot find symbol symbol : variable voteDelay location: class server.model.players.Client c.voteDelay = Long.toString(86400000 + System.currentTimeMillis( )); ^ src\server\model\players\packets\Commands.java:476: cannot find symbol symbol : variable puremaster location: class server.model.players.Client c.puremaster = 1; ^ Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 3 errors Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
I get this error. Can someone please tell me whats wrong with it. I took out the c. so its now just "voteDelay" and made the long.parseLong to just Long and still can't get rid of that vote error. This is the first error message, not the one I get after making my adjustments. Its the same though, the errors are in the same place.
